# Implementation Plan - Chatbot Widget Integration

The goal is to enable your RAG Chatbot to be embedded into any external website as a floating widget (a button in the corner that opens the chat window).

## Proposed Architecture
We will use an **Iframe-based Widget** approach. This is the industry standard for chatbots (like Intercom or Drift) because:
1.  **Isolation**: The chatbot's CSS won't conflict with the host website's CSS.
2.  **Security**: The chat session is secure within your domain.
3.  **Simplicity**: The host website only needs to add one line of code.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> Ensure your hosting provider (where you deploy this Flask app) allows usage in Iframes. Most do by default, but some strict security headers might need adjustment.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Backend Updates
#### [MODIFY] [app.py](file:///c:/Users/sunda/OneDrive/Desktop/Reput%20project/RAGchatbot_reput/app.py)
- Add a new route `@app.route('/widget')`.
- This route will serve a simplified version of the chat interface specifically designed for small windows.
- (Optional) Configure `CORS` if we need to allow the external site to ping an API availability check.

### 2. Frontend Updates
#### [NEW] [templates/widget.html](file:///c:/Users/sunda/OneDrive/Desktop/Reput%20project/RAGchatbot_reput/templates/widget.html)
- A streamlined version of [index.html](file:///c:/Users/sunda/OneDrive/Desktop/Reput%20project/RAGchatbot_reput/templates/index.html).
- Removes the large "Jeremy" header and side margins.
- Optimized to fit 100% width/height of the small iframe.

#### [NEW] [static/js/embed.js](file:///c:/Users/sunda/OneDrive/Desktop/Reput%20project/RAGchatbot_reput/static/js/embed.js)
- This is the script external websites will load.
- It will:
    1.  Inject a "Chat via RePut" floating button to the bottom-right of the page.
    2.  Inject a hidden `iframe` pointing to your new `/widget` route.
    3.  Handle the toggle logic (Show/Hide chat window on click).

### 3. Styling
#### [MODIFY] [static/css/style.css](file:///c:/Users/sunda/OneDrive/Desktop/Reput%20project/RAGchatbot_reput/static/css/style.css)
- Add a `.widget-mode` class to adjust padding and shadows when running inside the iframe.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1.  **Local Test Page**: Create a simple `test_integration.html` file locally that mimics an external website.
2.  **Embed Code**: Add the `<script src="http://localhost:5000/static/js/embed.js"></script>` tag to it.
3.  **Functional Test**:
    - Open `test_integration.html`.
    - Verify the floating button appears.
    - Click the button and ensure the iframe opens the chat.
    - Send a message and verify the RAG bot responds correctly.
